.TH PRNFNT(1),User Commands,PRNFNT(1)

.SH NAME
prnfnt - print the current font as a character table

.SH SYNOPSIS
prnfnt

.SH DESCRIPTION
prnfnt prints every byte value 0x00..0xFF as a 16x16 grid using the currently loaded console font.
The header row shows the low nibble 0..F across the top;
the leftmost column of each row shows the high nibble.

Each cell is emitted with the CHROUT literal prefix byte 0x80, so control codes are rendered as their glyphs rather than being interpreted.

prnfnt takes no arguments.

.SH DISPLAY
On terminals at least 40 columns wide (the usual case), each row is separated by two blank lines so that 8-pixel-tall and 16-pixel-tall fonts both render cleanly.
On narrower terminals a single blank line is used so the grid still fits.

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: Table printed.

.SH SEE ALSO
font(1)
